Modifier Meaning <code>.once</code> exactly 1 call <code>.twice</code> exactly 2 calls <code>.thrice</code> exactly 3 calls <code>.times(n)</code> exactly N calls <code>.exactly(n)</code> alias for <code>.times(n)</code> <code>.at-least(n)</code> N or more calls <code>.at-most(n)</code> N or fewer calls <pre><code>expect($log).to.have-received('info').twice;
expect($log).to.have-received('info').at-least(2);
expect($log).to.have-received('info').at-most(3);
</code></pre> <p>Each chained modifier replaces any failure recorded by the previous step, so chains like <code>.have-received('m').with('a').twice</code> produce at most one failure even if the first check would have failed on its own.</p>
